_sText: A map for my mod: COUNTER STRIKE SOURCE ZERO

My God....
I finally did it...
Project Wintermaze_2016 is finally done at base level...

Back in 2016 I started 2 things, studying at a university and working on a map. You see I had just figured out how to deal with problems in Hammer, this essentially allowed me to make bigger, more complex maps. And I wanted to put my skills and efforts to the test... So i took an old idea I had for 1.6 and made these monsters of maps...Needless to say I learned alot, made several prefabs in the process and gained a massive headache in attempting to bend Hammer to my will...

About the map pack:

Player count for all maps: 20vs20

The map pack contains, in total 5 maps of varying sizes, that can be classified under "Fight Yard" sub category.  

If you are a simple individual, that doesn't want anything complex, V1 might be for you. If you want more fun and uncertanty, V4 and V5 might be more for you. Oh and those 2 maps have functioning trams and a helicopter. V5 also has an underground tunnel system, a bit larger then v3.

ALL MAPS HAVE A FUNCTIONING MINIMAP, 
I hope the green text in bold got your attention. All 5 maps have a functioning minimap, in case of V5 the minimap has 2 layers that switch, depending on if you are underground or on the surface, so that you dont get lost in the labirinth. 
And just because it's a maze, doesn't mean you'll get lost, i created it to be more of a series of corridors, rather then a maze you can get lost in. 

v1,2,3 Are quite simple maps. They're not as interactive, and are rather self explanitory. 

V4,5

 The maps are huge and took me a long time to get them up and running. 

They are quite interactive, not your standard layout, but you shouldn't get lost either.  I tried to make a relatively fun maps that would be interesting to play with friends, or to wage war against other clans. Control of certain parts of these maps can be useful as there certain things that can give you an advantage (helicopter, trams, armory, warehouse, CCTV room).  Oh and CCTV,helicopters and trams are all working. 

The V5 map also has an interactive minimap, which works on the top left of your screen. It should change, depending on if your in tunnels or on surface. 

The maps are quite large, very spacious, and sort of like an open world type thing. So not your typical layout. 

Final words:

This project was a test for myself as a mapper, to see what can i come up with and do. 

Hope you'll like it and will have fun!

Ah...Finaly... the Wintermaze V5 map is out! With this map the base of project wintermaze has been concluded. 

I cannot tell you enough how much of a pain it was to make this thing! 
See dev notes for extra info.

About the map: 

Player Count: 20vs20

Newest map as part of project "Wintermaze_2016".  The map is huge and took me a long time to get it up and running. 

The map is quite interactive, not your standard layout, but you shouldn't get lost either.  I tried to make a relatively fun map that would be interesting to play with friends, or to wage war against other clans. Control of certain parts of this map can be useful as there certain things that can give you an advantage (helicopter, trams, armory, warehouse, CCTV room).  Oh and CCTV,helicopters and trams are all working. 

The map also has an interactive minimap, which works on the top left of your screen. It should change, depending on if your in tunnels or on surface. 

The map itself is quite large, very spacious, and sort of like an open world type thing. So not your typical layout. 

This map was also a test for myself as a mapper, to see what can i come up with and do. 

Hope you'll like it and will have fun!

Instructions: 

When you download the map, every file will be in a folder, that has the same name as the folders in your steam directory.

bhop_museum2

This map functions in a similar way to bhop_museum1. It utilizes Tony's non-linear checkpoint system and the map can be completed in any variation. There are four wings in total, with the "north wing" being the last one to complete. 

West Wing - Features large hallways that lead into red art rooms with some models & features showcased. Mostly featured on artwork in antiquity. Most of the artwork is unique to the map but there is some featured from museum1

East Wing - A series of green, modern art rooms that are intertwined with each other. Not that the map itself is very "realistic", but this is probably the least immersive stage in the map.

Atrium/Cafe Wing - This "wing" features a hallway that connects you into a mini cafe section, then into an atrium and then into a temple that is currently being renovated. If I'm being honest, this wing was plagued with FPS issues so I had to scale back some of the things. Originally, there was a stonehenge model but I decided the extra FPS was more important.

North Wing - The North Wing is the last wing to be completed and features the checkpoint teleporter at the beginning of the hallway. This wing is inspired by the starting room in museum1, however it is unique. The end zone is on the 2nd story of the room.

Bonus 1 - The first bonus starts in a bathroom that is connected to one of the West Wing hallways. You bhop through both male and female bathrooms, into a vent, then you drop & spin into an office room, followed by a downstairs "basement-ish" room and then lastly a temple. In hindsight, it doesn't make sense to have a bathroom vent lead into an office, but the bonus' aren't meant to be super immersive. I was just having fun making them.

Bonus 2 - I was trying to go with some varied gameplay on the 2nd bonus. The bonus starts out with a booster and then the first half of the level is somewhat climby. The 2nd half is inside of a temple (kind of the like the start of the temple in the atrium level) and is more of a speedrun part. However, it is slightly technical and requires you to keep spin in tight spaces. 

I would like to thank everybody who has tested the map and gave me feedback/advice. This is probably the most time and effort I've put into a map, and even though some of the aesthetics fall a little flat, I think the map still turned out nicely. I wanted significantly more models, but around 75-85% of the models were unable to be used in source/turned out terribly after decompliation.

Enjoy the map!
